  "clinical_criteria": [
    "QRSd between 65-120ms",
    "Heart Rate between 50-100",
    "ECG recorded during presence of sodium channel blocking drugs excluded (flecainide, propafenone, mexiletine, lidocaine, quinidine, procainamide, disopyramide, amiodarone, imipramine, amitryptiline >25mg total daily dose, lithium, encainide, moricizine, quinine, desipramine, propoxyphene, tocainide)",
    "Lab values exclusion: K > 6, K < 3.5, Ca < 8, Ca > 11, Mg < 1.7 (labs must be +/- 48h from ECG time)",
    "Lab values exclusion: CPK-MB > 8, Troponin > 0.05 (positive cardiac enzymes), BNP > 100",
    "ECG Impression must not contain evidence of heart disease concepts (non-negated)",
    "Notes contain no evidence of heart disease concepts before ECG time or within one month following",
    "Study ECG is the first normal ECG",
    "Must have at least a problem list and/or note containing non-empty medication list and past medical history before or immediately after the ECG",
    "Natural Language Processing on ECG impression excludes all but negated terms (e.g., exclude possible, probable, or asserted bundle branch blocks)",
    "Exclude normalization negations like 'LBBB no longer present'",
    "Patients with DNA whose first electrocardiogram (ECG) is designated as normal and lacking an exclusion criteria",
    "Timeline: Y duration = from first entry in EMR until one month following normal ECG",
    "Timeline: Z duration = most recent clinic visit or problem list to one week following normal ECG"
  ],
  "algorithm_summary": "This phenotype identifies patients with normal QRS duration (65-120ms) for genetic determinants study. Cases and controls are drawn from the same population for continuous trait analysis, differing only by QRSd. The study ECG must be the first normal ECG (heart rate 50-100) without evidence of heart disease in the impression. Exclusions include: presence of sodium channel blocking drugs at ECG time, electrolyte abnormalities (K, Ca, Mg) within 48 hours, elevated cardiac enzymes or BNP, any ICD-9 codes or CPT codes for heart disease, NLP-detected heart disease concepts in notes/problem lists (before ECG or within 1 month after), and lack of documented medication list/past medical history. The algorithm uses extensive ICD-9 codes (93-V45.82), CPT codes (66-93652), and UMLS CUIs (C0001396-C0151744) to exclude coronary disease, heart failure, valvular disease, cardiomyopathy, arrhythmias, conduction disorders, and cardiac procedures.",
  "analysis_timestamp": "2026-05-02T19:56:29.855686Z"
}